<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How the Xas website handles your data — short version: it's a static site that doesn't track you."
  updated="5 June 2026"
>
  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>xas.band</strong> is a static website. It has no accounts, no sign-up forms,
    no advertising and no analytics or tracking cookies. We don’t build a profile of you,
    and we don’t sell or share personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>Who is responsible</h2>
  <p>
    This site is operated by <strong>Kash Sajadi</strong> (the artist Xas), who is the
    data controller for the limited processing described here. Contact:
    <a href="mailto:kash@xas.band">kash@xas.band</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What is collected</h2>
  <p>
    We don’t ask you for any personal information. The only data processed is the minimum
    that the internet requires to deliver a web page:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Hosting logs.</strong> The site is hosted on AWS (Amplify / CloudFront).
      Like any web host, AWS automatically records standard request data — such as your IP
      address, browser type, the pages requested and the time — to serve the site and keep
      it secure. These logs are handled by AWS as our processor.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Web fonts.</strong> The site loads typefaces from third-party font services
      (rsms.me for Inter, Google Fonts, and Fontshare). When your browser fetches a font,
      that provider receives your IP address and request headers. This is solely to render
      the typography; we receive nothing back.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    There are no first- or third-party tracking cookies set by this site. If that ever
    changes, this page and the “last updated” date will be revised first.
  </p>

  <h2>Links to other platforms</h2>
  <p>
    Where the site links out to streaming services (SoundCloud, Spotify, Apple Music,
    YouTube, Bandcamp) or you email us, those services receive whatever you choose to share
    with them under their own privacy policies. We have no control over their practices.
  </p>

  <h2>If you email us</h2>
  <p>
    If you contact <a href="mailto:kash@xas.band">kash@xas.band</a>, we keep your message
    and email address only as long as needed to reply and to keep a record of the
    correspondence. We don’t add you to any mailing list.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct or delete personal
    data we hold about you, and to know how it is used. We don’t sell personal information.
    Because this site collects so little, in practice this usually concerns hosting logs or
    any email you’ve sent us. To exercise a right, email
    <a href="mailto:kash@xas.band">kash@xas.band</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    This site is a general-audience music page and is not directed at children, and we do
    not knowingly collect personal data from anyone.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy as the site evolves. The “last updated” date above always
    reflects the current version.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Privacy questions? Email <a href="mailto:kash@xas.band">kash@xas.band</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
